+// ── Export / Import ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+//
+// We expose two endpoints that wrap the on-disk format gitnexus already uses:
+//
+//   GET  /export?repo=<name>&mode=index|bundle
+//        Streams a ZIP. mode=index packages just <repoPath>/.gitnexus/.
+//        mode=bundle packages the entire <repoPath> minus heavy junk
+//        (node_modules, .git, dist, ...). meta.json is rewritten so the
+//        receiver doesn't inherit our absolute path.
+//
+//   POST /import?targetPath=<abs>&mode=index|bundle  (body: application/zip)
+//        Extracts the uploaded ZIP under <targetPath>, fixes meta.json's
+//        repoPath to match, and registers the repo by hitting /api/analyze
+//        on the gitnexus server (force=false → it reuses the existing index).
+//
+// We use the busybox zip/unzip binaries (added in Dockerfile.web) instead of
+// pulling a Node zip dep, because the docker-server runtime is dependency-free
+// today and we want to keep it that way.
